The article highlights the potential consequences of a government shutdown caused by extreme House Republicans. It criticizes their partisan approach and contrasts it with the Senate's bipartisan action. The shutdown would affect small businesses, particularly in terms of loan processing and access to federal contracting opportunities. It also mentions the closure of Small Business Administration district offices, which would hinder assistance to thousands of Americans. The article emphasizes the importance of small business support and blames extreme House Republicans for jeopardizing funding for vital programs. It concludes by providing a state-by-state estimate of the financial losses small businesses would face each day during a government shutdown.